    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Wood of the species Gleditsia triacanthos, native to regions in North and South America, Africa, and Asia. It produces a high quality wood that polishes well, but is lighter and weaker than most locust wood. It is used for specialty furniture, wheel spokes, and posts.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
